# Allowlist, not a denylist. This directory is both the source tree and the deployment
# root, so runtime data accumulates next to the code: the job result cache, the redis
# volume, and the PubChem index the vectordb service mounts, which runs to tens of
# gigabytes. Naming those to exclude them is fragile, since anything added later is sent
# to the build daemon by default. Ignoring everything and listing what `vite build`
# actually needs keeps the context at a few megabytes whatever else lands here.
*

